LukeW | UX Lisbon: Design Games
&ldquo;At User Experience Lisbon (UX LX), Donna Spencer talked about Design Games you can play with your team and with potential users of your product to elicit ideations and information in fun ways. Here&rsquo;s my notes from her presentation:&rdquo;
(tags: ux ia games design techniques tools userexperience informationarchitecture)

jQuery Masonry · David DeSandro
&ldquo;Masonry is a layout plugin for jQuery. Think of it as the flip side of CSS floats. Whereas floating arranges elements horizontally then vertically, Masonry arranges elements vertically then horizontally according to a grid. The result minimizes vertical gaps between elements of varying height, just like a mason fitting stones in a wall.&rdquo;
(tags: jquery layout css design userinterface userinterfacedesign ux ui code)

Apple - Support - Discussions - How to use TabBar in viewbase &hellip;
