(tags: htaccess hierarchicaltaskanalysis uk userexperience analysis tools)

japh&reg;: &ldquo;Newbie&rdquo; Feedback
&ldquo;I recently had the privilege to supply the challenge for the second ever Ruby Programming Challenge For Newbies. I thought it pretty cool that the challenge provoked 40+ &ldquo;newbies&rdquo; to submit responses. As one might expect, there was some rough Ruby, but very few butcherings of the language.
In the spirit of the code review, I tried to provide constructive feedback to all participants. Following is a summary of some common suggestions that I had to offer&hellip;&rdquo;

CodeIgniter - Open source PHP web application framework
&ldquo;Welcome to CodeIgniter!
CodeIgniter is a powerful PHP framework with a very small footprint, built for PHP coders who need a simple and elegant toolkit to create full-featured web applications. If you&rsquo;re a developer who lives in the real world of shared hosting accounts and clients with deadlines, and if you&rsquo;re tired of ponderously large and thoroughly undocumented frameworks&rdquo;

brandstorming: List of Social Media Interview Questions
&ldquo;So I saw the job description, but decided to create my own list of interview questions for social media consultants. This is a bit more involved than just blogging, but if want a job like this, or are hiring for a job like this, you could do a lot worse then to add these to your job description&rdquo;
(tags: socialmedia recruitment interviews interview)

scraplab : my last day at headshift
&ldquo;I have no expectation of what happens next, but here’s a manifesto. Being interesting is as important as being useful. Making things that delight and inspire is as important as creating value. Old systems are crumbling; the best you can do is be nimble, smart and make some trouble.&rdquo;
Tom&rsquo;s manifesto for what he&rsquo;s going to do next. I can&rsquo;t wait to see what he comes up with.

R.I.P. Enterprise RSS - ReadWriteWeb
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s with a heavy heart and a sense of bewilderment that we conclude that the market for enterprise-specific RSS readers appears to be dead. Two years ago there were three major players offering software that delivered information to the computers of business users via RSS. Today it looks to us like the demand simply never arose and that market is over.&rdquo;
A somewhat-flawed analysis that gets comprehensively fisked in the comments&hellip;

Locus Online Features: Cory Doctorow: Writing in the Age of Distraction
&ldquo;I think I&rsquo;ve managed to balance things out through a few simple techniques that I&rsquo;ve been refining for years. I still sometimes feel frazzled and info-whelmed, but that&rsquo;s rare. Most of the time, I&rsquo;m on top of my workload and my muse. Here&rsquo;s how I do it&rdquo;
(tags: writing tools techniques doctorow corydoctorow author)

Egg Mortgage calculator page
Egg&rsquo;s interactive mortgage calculator - works out the effect of over and underpayments. Witness the miracle of compound interest&hellip;
(tags: mortgage calculations calculator money)

From the BBC: &ldquo;Patient files &lsquo;more accessible&rsquo;&ldquo;
 The health service is to invest £300m in the next 10 years in information and communication technology.
The investment will mean that anyone in the health service, whether they are in a GP&rsquo;s surgery or a hospital ward, can access a patient&rsquo;s records.
 I sincerely hope that it&rsquo;s NOT going to allow ANYONE in the Health Service to access a patient&rsquo;s records&hellip;

How to Create a Super Shiny Pencil Icon - PSDTUTS
&ldquo;
The Pencil is one of the visual metaphors most used to express creativity. In this tutorial, I&rsquo;ll show you how to draw a pencil icon. We&rsquo;ll have a look at gradients, selection tools, and basic transform operations. Let&rsquo;s have some fun with this.&rdquo;
